<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Ixath">Ixath</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:35 p.m. 6/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Pk balancing for wizard types<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2090" TARGET=_self>Pk balancing for wizard types</A> (Ghouldan)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>This is probablly off the subject sorta.. but when everyone is complaining about Wizards being overpowered, they should look at the other casting classes with pets. A level 20 magician does about 25-45 damage LESS than a wizard of the same level, and he gets a pet. Necromancers, well..they're just overpowered. A level 12 necromancer was soloing kodiaks.. comeon, isint this overpowered? Wizards are fine, so what if they raid naked? They can be hit easier. If any of you warriors are complaining about being able to be killed by them easy, your not a very good player i guess.. just get some MR items and you wont be rooted very easy... and if you jump them (and you can run) they wont have time to get a spell off..

<BR>Shrug, stop whining about classes that are fine, and lower some of the other ones.. Hell, i even think clerics do to much damage and i play one..
<BR>oh well..
<P>Ixath -Dark Brigade-
<BR>Dark Elf Cleric
<BR>
